<plot>Theresa's life revolves around weekly visits to her father's grave where she performs ceremonial offerings of love and respect with a piece of smoked salmon. Mourning becomes easier than letting go until she meets Will, the cemetery groundskeeper, whose encounters with Theresa change everything. Sensitive and poignant, ONCE A FISH explores death within the continuum of life, where the certainty of ritual and the spontaneity of hope both have their place.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?411751</url></doc>
